TradeTongueTrade LanguageFamily: Han ( a la Sinitic: Chinese, Mandarin, Bai )SubGroup: HanAlphabet: DraconicRegions Spoken:  Kara TurDificulty: 2Spoken by many merchants, traders, and sailors, this language provides a common language for business. It's limited vocabulary consists mostly of trading and money exchanging terms. A growing number of diplomats use it for negotiating because it provides a neutral ground not favoring any one side's language.